Package org.rcsb.demo.MBT

Demos here are intended to exercise just the MBT.

See:
          Description

Class Summary
DumpPeriodicTable Dump the internal periodic table.
SimpleReadStructureDemo This first demo will read a structure file (.pdb{.gz} or .xml{.gz} specified from the command line) and create a structure, then traverse the structure by chain and output some interesting information about the structure components.
 

Package org.rcsb.demo.MBT Description

Demos here are intended to exercise just the MBT.

Some notes on the enclosed demos:

SimpleReadStructureDemo.java
This simply reads a structure and then dumps it in reports. Two salient issues, here:
    This should only require the org.rcsb.mbt.model and the org.rcsb.mbt.structLoader packages. You should be able to run this against the corresponding output jars and get no unresolveds. (To do this, you need to copy out the jars and copy out the source into its own directory, compile and run.) If you do get unresolveds, it means some dependency has incurred itself into the model that shouldn't be there.
DumpPeriodicTable
The MBT carries an internal representation of the periodic table. This dumps it. Note the color and radius are default and VDW, respectively. They may be changed by a mutator to reflect some other information for actual rendering.
org.rcsb.mbt.model.attributes package for further information.
